OL,3,CMore protection for victims as
OL,4,CGovernment vows crackdown on stalking
OL,6,FThis will stop offenders from
OL,7,Fcontacting their victims from prison,
OL,8,Fthe department said.
OL,10,FIf someone is acquitted, courts will
OL,11,Fstill have the power to apply
OL,12,Fprotection orders directly if there is
OL,13,Fenough evidence to suggest that the
OL,14,Fperson is still a risk to someone, the
OL,15,FHome Office added.
OL,17,FThe Government has also promised a
OL,18,Freview of stalking legislation to
OL,19,Fdetermine whether the law could be
OL,20,Fchanged to support police to better
OL,21,Fidentify stalking and arrest offenders.
